data.description: views! views! This beautiful home with exceptional water views of lake which then leads to canals that connect to the Withlacoochee River, with a private dock to place your boat and take fun trips to the lake and enjoy the beautiful nature and the beautiful sunsets. Consisting of three bedrooms, two baths, 1,551 sqft of living space, 3,909 sqft of total construction and almost an acre of land. This property has a large lot with a double access driveway for the entry and exit of cars, then we arrive at the large fully screened portal and luxurious details to receive visits. The entire house was completely remodeled with a spacious living room with a fireplace, new waterproof vinyl wooden floors and enough that it can be used as a second living room, game room, second dining room, etc; a dining room with sufficient lighting and luxurious details of decorations on the walls and doors. A spacious kitchen with granite countertops, wooden furniture and stainless steel appliances. The main bedroom with fine details in the ceiling, floor and door moldings; with walking closet for his and hers, with remodeled tiled bathrooms with niches. The rear terrace is fully screened and has enough space for your parties and meetings where you can appreciate the view of the lake. A huge garage that can also be used as a workshop since one part provides a workbench with pegboard walls that allows for a great organization of tools, while the other provides optimal storage for cars, atv's, lawn equipment, and more; It has capacity for more than 3 vehicles and a carport for 4 more cars. Less than 20 minutes from the city of Bushnell, Inverness and 1:15 from the city of Orlando and Tampa, this location gives you the quietness of the countryside while still hosting all the amenities that the city have to offer from shopping to entertainment, to restaurants, hospitals and much more!  Motivated seller, make your offer lets talk!!!!  The seller will concession  $10,000 for repairs , or  for closing cost, depending on what buyer wants to use it for.
